                            <li class="about-us__li">the requested web page</li>
                            <li class="about-us__li">the domain from which you access the Internet </li>
                            <li class="about-us__li">the date and time you access our site</li>
                            <li class="about-us__li">status of the request (e.g. success or failure)</li>
                            <li class="about-us__li">the type and version of your web browser (Firefox, Explorer, etc.)
                            </li>
                            <li class="about-us__li">Patients Who Can Receive Your Plasma: O-, O+</li>
                            <li class="about-us__li">the operating system (Windows, Mac, Unix, etc.) of the machine
                                running the web browser
                            </li>
                        </ul>
                        <p class="blood__p">
                            OneBlood will not obtain any other personally identifying information about you when you
                            visit our site, unless you choose to provide such information to us. Any information you
                            provide to us is securely stored within the OneBlood private network. Unless you ask us not
                            to, we may contact you via email in the future to tell you about OneBlood activities,
                            opportunities to donate blood in your area or changes to this privacy policy. We will not
                            share your information with any third party outside of our organization, other than as
                            necessary to fulfill a request you make, such as scheduling an appointment to give blood.
                            Any other dissemination of information will require your prior consent.
                        </p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="blood__label">
                        <h2 class="blood__h2">Surveys & Contests</h2>
